EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

10/15/2019

ALTIVIA Specialty Chemicals, LLC - La Porte, Tx (ALTIVIA)



The Environment, Health and Safety Policy of ALTIVIA Specialty Chemicals, LLC - La Porte, Tx is "to manufacture, sell, and distribute products worldwide in a manner that is safe and protective of our employees, neighbors, customers and other stakeholders, and the environment."  In fulfilling this policy, ALTIVIA Specialty Chemicals, LLC - La Porte, Tx has made a commitment to follow several guiding principles including:



* providing a safe and healthful workplace for our employees;

* operating our facilities  to prevent harm to public health and the environment;

* assuring that ALTIVIA Specialty Chemicals, LLC products can be produced, distributed, used, and disposed of safely; 

* alerting potentially affected persons to known or reasonably foreseeable hazards of our products and activities and informing them about proper protective measures; 

* contributing to the public's understanding and management of any significant risks arising from our products or activities;

* training, equipping and supporting all employees in the management and implementation of environment, health, safety and security activities at our facilities; and 

* compliance with applicable laws and regulations concerning environment, health and safety.



 ALTIVIA is committed to the Responsible Care voluntary initiative for safe management of chemicals.  ALTIVIA follows the Responsible Care Codes of Management Practice, which are integral to the implementation of the ALTIVIA's  Environment, Health & Safety Policy.   The Responsible Care Community Awareness Code of Management Practice and ALTIVIA's Community Awareness and Emergency Response (CAER) Policy are designed to assure emergency preparedness and to foster community right-to-know.  CAER Policy requires the La Porte plant to have a pro-active community awareness and emergency response program to handle emergencies that might happen in that f
